    "source_sections": {
      "references": "[ErKa46] Erd\\H{o}s, Paul and Kaplansky, Irving, The asymptotic number of Latin rectangles. Amer. J. Math. (1946), 230-236.\n \n [Ya51] Yamamoto, Koichi, On the asymptotic number of Latin rectangles. Jpn. J. Math. (1951), 113-119.",
      "remarks": "Erd\\H{o}s and Kaplansky \\cite{ErKa46} proved the count is\\[\\sim e^{-\\binom{k}{2}}(n!)^k\\]when $k=o((\\log n)^{3/2-\\epsilon})$. Yamamoto \\cite{Ya51} extended this to $k\\leq n^{1/3-o(1)}$.\n\nThe count of such Latin rectangles is A001009 in the OEIS."
    },
